name: EA-005-Maquiável
description:
Machiavelli (1469 - 1527 aC) was a Florentine Renaissance philosopher, historian, poet, diplomat, and musician. He is recognized as the founder of modern political thought and science, having written about the state and government as they really are, not as they ought to be.

Digital Watercolor Vector Illustration made in Adobe Photoshop, 1200x1200px, 200dpi, JPEG
